<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.250078>
    dc:description "FIGURES 17 – 19. Gymnetis pudibunda feeding on ripened fruits on the plants: 17 – 18, on “ black figs ”, together with flies, and black ants Acromyrmex lundi (Hymenoptera: Formicidae) (José C. Paz, Buenos Aires, Argentina, photographs by Alejandro Borquez); 19, on “ white figs ”, together with undetermined ants (locality and author of the photograph unknown, but by the phenotype of G. pudibunda, the photograph was taken in the province of Buenos Aires, see Di Iorio 2013)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/250078/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.250077>
    dc:description "FIGURES 13 – 16. Gymnetis pudibunda feeding on sap from adult and larval galleries of Megaplatypus mutatus (Coleoptera: Platypodidae) on the bole of Salix humboldtiana (Reserva Ecológica de Vicente López, Buenos Aires, Argentina): Fig. 13, adult gallery (see the air bubbles located in the entrance of the gallery), together with Compsocerus violaceous (Coleoptera: Cerambycidae) (photograph by Lucas Damer, 17 December 2012); Fig. 14, larval gallery, 21 December 2012; Fig. 15, adult gallery together with ants (photograph by Rocío Gonzalez, 7 January 2012); Fig. 16, adult gallery together with G. chalcipes and C. violaceus, 2 January 2013." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/250077/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

